<item xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="3" xml:id="addition3" syriacatags="colophon-incertus">
    <locus from="236a"/>
    <p>Under the final rubric we read:</p>
    <p>
        <quote xml:lang="syr"> ܦܚܡ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܬܐܘܡܐ ܡܢ ܥܘܡܪܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ ܕܝܚ̈ܝܕܝܐ ܕܩܠܬ , ܟܠ ܕܩ̇ܪܐ ܢܨܠܐ ܥܠܘܗܝ. ܐܠܗܐ ܚܘܢܝܗܝ </quote>
    </p>
    <p>
        <quote>
            <persName>Thomas</persName>, from the holy <placeName>convent of the monks of Kellat</placeName>, collated this book. Let every one who reads, pray for him: 'May God have mercy on him.'</quote> See <bibl>Assemani, Bibl. Orient., t. ii.,p. 231</bibl>.</p>
