<item xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1" xml:id="addition1">
    <locus from="50b" to="50b"/>
    <p>On fol. 50 b there is a note, which, besides being stained and torn, has twice suffered alteration and erasure. Of the original writing we can read, in the first and second lines, the words:</p>
    <p>
        <quote xml:lang="syr">ܒܟܣܐ . . . ܫܢܬ ܬܫܥܡܐܐ ܘܥܣܪ ܙܒܝܢ . . .</quote>
    </p>
    <p>and below:</p>
    <p>
        <quote xml:lang="syr">ܡܢ ܛܝܒܘܬܐ ܕܐܠܗܐ ܕܝܠܗܘܢ ܥܒܕܘ ܠܗܘܢ ܟܬܒܐ . . . ܩܐ  ܕܡܙܡܘܪ̈ܐ ܠܩܕܝܫܐ</quote>
    </p>
    <p>which show that the book was purchased by, and in all likelihood written for, certain persons in the year <origDate when-custom="0910" datingMethod="Seleucid">910</origDate>, A.D. <origDate when="0599" calendar="Gregorian">599</origDate>. </p>
